comments.body:
@sam-github 

> Given the uncommon nature of that use-case, ...

Actually, we have a problem with this functionality.

Legacy Client App (calls an API endpoint **w HTTP/1 over TLS**) -> Load Balancer with SSL termination (calls an API endpoint **w HTTP/1.1 wo TLS**) -> API Endpoint with Node.js `node:http2 createServer` , called with **HTTP/1.1 wo TLS** throws an error

As you can see, `node:http` is not interchangeable with `node:http2`. This is a serious problem, because an architectural modification is required (changing place of SSL termination), or the old code must be kept alongside the new one.

@mcollina What do you think?

